node.text:
This Halloween we decided to throw a Hocus Pocus themed family party at home, and watch the movie now available on Digital in 4K Ultra HD. October is going to be a crazy month for us! We’ll be packing up and moving to Nashville but I’m not sure if we’ll make it in time for Halloween. So instead, we decided to celebrate Halloween at home, before the move, and the kids LOVED IT! #ad 
.
.
We made Spellbook Brownies, Mummy Dogs, Dead Mans Toes, Life Potion, and Amuck-Amuck-AMUNCH (watch the video for how-to’s). Combine that with a fog machine, trick-or-treating around the house, and a Hocus Pocus movie night and you’ve got yourself a Halloween Party! We watch the beloved classic Hocus Pocus every year but this year it was crystal clear on the big screen in 4K Ultra HD and it always serves as the BEST kickoff to our holiday season. 
.
.
What are your plans for Halloween?
@disney #hocuspocus

node.text:
I just need this pic to have a place right here. 
.
.
I should start by saying that this is not in ANY way meant to be a political post, so please don’t take it as that. 
.
.
The world is just so upside down right now. I don’t know about you, but over the past couple of years I’ve grown increasingly confused as to whom I can trust. The media is full of sensational headlines and scare tactics, our government officials contradict themselves and leave me feeling more confused than ever. I keep feeling like no matter what—I don’t know where to turn to or whom to trust for direction and answers? 
.
.
And then I sat in my hallway last week and took this pic. It’s like I had forgotten who’s really in charge here. Some might unfollow for me posting a picture of Christ—and that’s fine. But this is my public declaration that this is MY leader. And I am His follower. I know who wins in the end. So this is me, surrendering my will, buckling up and trying to enjoy the ride. Hopefully this picture brings you peace, if that’s what you’re searching for. 🤍

node.text:
Getting some good use out of Rae’s Retreat (craft room ✂️)…which is good bc since converting this space we have ZERO storage space in this house anymore. 😬🤭 But it’s ALL worth it for this little girl. 
.
.
This week we got to try Cricut’s newest smart cutting machine—The Cricut Maker 3 and my mind is blown! 🤯 It can cut over 300+ materials and doesn’t even require a cutting mat! It engraves, debosses, cuts through thick leather and even some types of wood! 😳 Sky’s the limit when DIYing, crafting, and creating with the Cricut Maker 3! And don’t forget this cute little gift wrapping station that we turned into our Cricut Cart. It stores all of our vinyl + supplies AND holds those pesky tubes of gift wrap. 🙌🏻
.
.
Now for the fun part, will you believe me when I tell you that I got BOTH of these items (the Cricut + Craft Cart) at homedepot.com/decor? Welp, I did. 👏🏻 So many incredible items for your home in that section of their website. Look there and check out their affordable prices before buying on other websites. Their selections and vast offerings will surprise you!! @homedepot #HomeDepotPartner #HomeDepotDecor
